{
  "texts": [
    "These radar systems provide valuable insights into target characteristics such as range and velocity through the analysis of the signals they produce [25,26].Figure 1(a) depicts a simplified block diagram of the BGT60TR13C chipset, which retains only a single transmitter and receiver.",
    "On the transmitter side, a phase-locked loop (PLL) governs the linear frequency sweeping process.",
    "A reference oscillator at 80 MHz clocks the loop, and a finite state machine (FSM) controlled by the same reference clock generates a linear voltage ramp.",
    "This voltage ramp is applied to a voltage-controlled oscillator (VCO), which generates continuous signals known as chirps.",
    "These chirps exhibit linear frequency-modulated (LFM) characteristics, spanning a frequency range from 58.5 to 62.5 GHz for the proposed application."
  ]
}